HEADWORD: mamoncillo
<hw>mamoncillo</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tropical American tree
(<spn>Melicocca bijuga</spn>, or <spn>Melicocca bijugatus</spn>) bearing
a small edible fruit with green leathery skin and sweet juicy
translucent pulp.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Spanish lime, Spanish lime tree, honey berry, genip,
ginep, <spn>Melicocca bijuga</spn>, <spn>Melicocca
bijugatus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

